  "root_text": {
    "dhp273:0.1": "Khuddakanikāya ",
    "dhp273:0.2": "Dhammapada ",
    "dhp273:0.3": "Maggavagga ",
    "dhp273:0.4": "Pañcasatabhikkhuvatthu ",
    "dhp273:1": "Maggānaṭṭhaṅgiko seṭṭho, ",
    "dhp273:2": "saccānaṁ caturo padā; ",
    "dhp273:3": "Virāgo seṭṭho dhammānaṁ, ",
    "dhp273:4": "dvipadānañca cakkhumā. ",
    "dhp274:1": "Eseva maggo natthañño, ",
    "dhp274:2": "Dassanassa visuddhiyā; ",
    "dhp274:3": "Etañhi tumhe paṭipajjatha, ",
    "dhp274:4": "Mārassetaṁ pamohanaṁ. ",
    "dhp275:1": "Etañhi tumhe paṭipannā, ",
    "dhp275:2": "dukkhassantaṁ karissatha; ",
    "dhp275:3": "Akkhāto vo mayā maggo, ",
    "dhp275:4": "aññāya sallakantanaṁ. ",
    "dhp276:1": "Tumhehi kiccamātappaṁ, ",
    "dhp276:2": "akkhātāro tathāgatā; ",
    "dhp276:3": "Paṭipannā pamokkhanti, ",
    "dhp276:4": "jhāyino mārabandhanā. ",
    "dhp277:0": "Aniccalakkhaṇavatthu ",
    "dhp277:1": "“Sabbe saṅkhārā aniccā”ti, ",
    "dhp277:2": "yadā paññāya passati; ",
    "dhp277:3": "Atha nibbindati dukkhe, ",
    "dhp277:4": "esa maggo visuddhiyā. ",
    "dhp278:0": "Dukkhalakkhaṇavatthu ",
    "dhp278:1": "“Sabbe saṅkhārā dukkhā”ti, ",
    "dhp278:2": "yadā paññāya passati; ",
    "dhp278:3": "Atha nibbindati dukkhe, ",
    "dhp278:4": "esa maggo visuddhiyā. ",
    "dhp279:0": "Anattalakkhaṇavatthu ",
    "dhp279:1": "“Sabbe dhammā anattā”ti, ",
    "dhp279:2": "yadā paññāya passati; ",
    "dhp279:3": "Atha nibbindati dukkhe, ",
    "dhp279:4": "esa maggo visuddhiyā. ",
    "dhp280:0": "Padhānakammikatissattheravatthu ",
    "dhp280:1": "Uṭṭhānakālamhi anuṭṭhahāno, ",
    "dhp280:2": "Yuvā balī ālasiyaṁ upeto; ",
    "dhp280:3": "Saṁsannasaṅkappamano kusīto, ",
    "dhp280:4": "Paññāya maggaṁ alaso na vindati. ",
    "dhp281:0": "Sūkarapetavatthu ",
    "dhp281:1": "Vācānurakkhī manasā susaṁvuto, ",
    "dhp281:2": "Kāyena ca nākusalaṁ kayirā; ",
    "dhp281:3": "Ete tayo kammapathe visodhaye, ",
    "dhp281:4": "Ārādhaye maggamisippaveditaṁ. ",
    "dhp282:0": "Poṭṭhilattheravatthu ",
    "dhp282:1": "Yogā ve jāyatī bhūri, ",
    "dhp282:2": "ayogā bhūrisaṅkhayo; ",
    "dhp282:3": "Etaṁ dvedhāpathaṁ ñatvā, ",
    "dhp282:4": "bhavāya vibhavāya ca; ",
    "dhp282:5": "Tathāttānaṁ niveseyya, ",
    "dhp282:6": "yathā bhūri pavaḍḍhati. ",
    "dhp283:0": "Pañcamahallakabhikkhuvatthu ",
    "dhp283:1": "Vanaṁ chindatha mā rukkhaṁ, ",
    "dhp283:2": "vanato jāyate bhayaṁ; ",
    "dhp283:3": "Chetvā vanañca vanathañca, ",
    "dhp283:4": "nibbanā hotha bhikkhavo. ",
    "dhp284:1": "Yāva hi vanatho na chijjati, ",
    "dhp284:2": "Aṇumattopi narassa nārisu; ",
    "dhp284:3": "Paṭibaddhamanova tāva so, ",
    "dhp284:4": "Vaccho khīrapakova mātari. ",
    "dhp285:0": "Suvaṇṇakārattheravatthu ",
    "dhp285:1": "Ucchinda sinehamattano, ",
    "dhp285:2": "Kumudaṁ sāradikaṁva pāṇinā; ",
    "dhp285:3": "Santimaggameva brūhaya, ",
    "dhp285:4": "Nibbānaṁ sugatena desitaṁ. ",
    "dhp286:0": "Mahādhanavāṇijavatthu ",
    "dhp286:1": "Idha vassaṁ vasissāmi, ",
    "dhp286:2": "idha hemantagimhisu; ",
    "dhp286:3": "Iti bālo vicinteti, ",
    "dhp286:4": "antarāyaṁ na bujjhati. ",
    "dhp287:0": "Kisāgotamīvatthu ",
    "dhp287:1": "Taṁ puttapasusammattaṁ, ",
    "dhp287:2": "byāsattamanasaṁ naraṁ; ",
    "dhp287:3": "Suttaṁ gāmaṁ mahoghova, ",
    "dhp287:4": "maccu ādāya gacchati. ",
    "dhp288:0": "Paṭācārāvatthu ",
    "dhp288:1": "Na santi puttā tāṇāya, ",
    "dhp288:2": "na pitā nāpi bandhavā; ",
    "dhp288:3": "Antakenādhipannassa, ",
    "dhp288:4": "natthi ñātīsu tāṇatā. ",
    "dhp289:1": "Etamatthavasaṁ ñatvā, ",
    "dhp289:2": "paṇḍito sīlasaṁvuto; ",
    "dhp289:3": "Nibbānagamanaṁ maggaṁ, ",
    "dhp289:4": "khippameva visodhaye. ",
    "dhp289:5": "Maggavaggo vīsatimo. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "dhp273:0.1": "Minor Collection ",
    "dhp273:0.2": "Sayings of the Dhamma 273–289 ",
    "dhp273:0.3": "20. The Path ",
    "dhp273:0.4": "",
    "dhp273:1": "Of paths, the eightfold is the best; ",
    "dhp273:2": "of truths, the four statements; ",
    "dhp273:3": "dispassion is the best of things, ",
    "dhp273:4": "and the Clear-eyed One is the best of humans. ",
    "dhp274:1": "<em>This</em> is the path, there is no other ",
    "dhp274:2": "for the purification of vision. ",
    "dhp274:3": "You all must practice this, ",
    "dhp274:4": "it is the way to baffle Māra. ",
    "dhp275:1": "When you all are practicing this, ",
    "dhp275:2": "you will make an end of suffering. ",
    "dhp275:3": "I have explained the path to you ",
    "dhp275:4": "for extracting the thorn with wisdom. ",
    "dhp276:1": "You yourselves must do the work, ",
    "dhp276:2": "the Realized Ones just show the way. ",
    "dhp276:3": "Meditators practicing absorption ",
    "dhp276:4": "are released from Māra’s bonds. ",
    "dhp277:0": "",
    "dhp277:1": "All conditions are impermanent—",
    "dhp277:2": "when this is seen with wisdom, ",
    "dhp277:3": "one grows disillusioned with suffering: ",
    "dhp277:4": "this is the path to purity. ",
    "dhp278:0": "",
    "dhp278:1": "All conditions are suffering—",
    "dhp278:2": "when this is seen with wisdom, ",
    "dhp278:3": "one grows disillusioned with suffering: ",
    "dhp278:4": "this is the path to purity. ",
    "dhp279:0": "",
    "dhp279:1": "All things are not-self—",
    "dhp279:2": "when this is seen with wisdom, ",
    "dhp279:3": "one grows disillusioned with suffering: ",
    "dhp279:4": "this is the path to purity. ",
    "dhp280:0": "",
    "dhp280:1": "They don’t get going when it’s time to start; ",
    "dhp280:2": "they’re young and strong, but given to sloth. ",
    "dhp280:3": "Their mind depressed in sunken thought, ",
    "dhp280:4": "lazy and slothful, they can’t discern the path. ",
    "dhp281:0": "",
    "dhp281:1": "Guarded in speech, restrained in mind, ",
    "dhp281:2": "doing no unskillful bodily deed. ",
    "dhp281:3": "Purify these three ways of performing deeds, ",
    "dhp281:4": "and win the path known to seers. ",
    "dhp282:0": "",
    "dhp282:1": "From meditation springs wisdom, ",
    "dhp282:2": "without meditation, wisdom ends. ",
    "dhp282:3": "Knowing these two paths—",
    "dhp282:4": "of progress and decline—",
    "dhp282:5": "you should conduct yourself ",
    "dhp282:6": "so that wisdom grows. ",
    "dhp283:0": "",
    "dhp283:1": "Cut down the jungle, not just a tree; ",
    "dhp283:2": "from the jungle springs fear. ",
    "dhp283:3": "Having cut down jungle and snarl, ",
    "dhp283:4": "be free of jungles, mendicants! ",
    "dhp284:1": "So long as the vine, no matter how small, ",
    "dhp284:2": "that ties a man to women is not cut, ",
    "dhp284:3": "his mind remains trapped, ",
    "dhp284:4": "like a calf suckling its mother. ",
    "dhp285:0": "",
    "dhp285:1": "Cut out affection for oneself, ",
    "dhp285:2": "like plucking an autumn lotus. ",
    "dhp285:3": "Foster only the path to peace, ",
    "dhp285:4": "the extinguishment the Holy One taught. ",
    "dhp286:0": "",
    "dhp286:1": "“Here I will stay for the rains; ",
    "dhp286:2": "here for winter, here the summer”; ",
    "dhp286:3": "thus the fool thinks, ",
    "dhp286:4": "not realizing the danger. ",
    "dhp287:0": "",
    "dhp287:1": "As a mighty flood sweeps away a sleeping village, ",
    "dhp287:2": "death steals away a man ",
    "dhp287:3": "who dotes on children and cattle, ",
    "dhp287:4": "his mind caught up in them. ",
    "dhp288:0": "",
    "dhp288:1": "Children provide you no shelter, ",
    "dhp288:2": "nor does father, nor relatives. ",
    "dhp288:3": "When you’re seized by the terminator, ",
    "dhp288:4": "there’s no shelter in family. ",
    "dhp289:1": "Knowing the reason for this, ",
    "dhp289:2": "astute, and ethically restrained, ",
    "dhp289:3": "one would quickly clear the path ",
    "dhp289:4": "that leads to extinguishment. ",
    "dhp289:5": ""
  },
